110
00:07:10,460 --> 00:07:13,280
as a Chinese nationalist patriot.

111
00:07:13,280 --> 00:07:17,130
And then being, unlike in the former Soviet Union, not only

112
00:07:17,130 --> 00:07:20,370
the leader of the revolution, like Lenin in Russia,

113
00:07:20,370 --> 00:07:24,230
but also the leader of the communist state

114
00:07:24,230 --> 00:07:27,780
as it developed its sinews use of power, like Stalin,

115
00:07:27,780 --> 00:07:31,370
in the Soviet Union, Mao sort of combined

116
00:07:31,370 --> 00:07:37,950
in himself both the image of a young, nationalist, revolutionary firebrand

117
00:07:37,950 --> 00:07:42,450
and at the same time a mature communist leader

118
00:07:42,450 --> 00:07:46,190
who presided over a very powerful state.

119
00:07:46,190 --> 00:07:50,030
And so he is an image of nationalism to most Chinese.

120
00:07:50,030 --> 00:07:53,500
He is an image of Chinese strength.

121
00:07:53,500 --> 00:07:56,410
He is also an image of Chinese tradition.

122
00:07:56,410 --> 00:08:00,580
His propensity to spout earthy aphorisms, when

123
00:08:00,580 --> 00:08:04,200
that seemed appropriate; his use of a Chinese calligraphy

124
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:08,380
penned to write poetry, when that seemed appropriate.

125
00:08:08,380 --> 00:08:13,320
He wielded a variety of cultural weapons that

126
00:08:13,320 --> 00:08:17,930
are associated with political power in the Chinese tradition.

127
00:08:17,930 --> 00:08:19,400
He did so very skillfully.

128
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:24,720
And so his image, I would say, is an exceedingly complicated one in China.

129
00:08:24,720 --> 00:08:31,040
