152
00:10:00,910 --> 00:10:06,830
That it was Mao's revolution that put a very strong Chinese Communist Party

153
00:10:06,830 --> 00:10:08,840
in place in China.

154
00:10:08,840 --> 00:10:14,630
And the current leadership, Xi Jinping, is a so-called princeling.

155
00:10:14,630 --> 00:10:22,450
He has his position because his father was a revolutionary comrade of Mao's.

156
00:10:22,450 --> 00:10:27,270
And for this generation, this generation of the children of the revolutionaries,

157
00:10:27,270 --> 00:10:30,480
their political legitimacy is very closely

158
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:34,300
intertwined with and dependent upon that of the revolution and Mao

159
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:37,480
as the acknowledged leader of that revolution.

160
00:10:37,480 --> 00:10:41,520
So I think it's a very complicated legacy.

161
00:10:41,520 --> 00:10:44,880
And it's different in different places.

162
00:10:44,880 --> 00:10:47,490
It's different among different age groups.

163
00:10:47,490 --> 00:10:51,010
It's different among different social classes.

164
00:10:51,010 --> 00:10:55,110
But it's also extremely different from the situation in the former Soviet

165
00:10:55,110 --> 00:10:56,470
Union or Eastern Europe.

166
00:10:56,470 --> 00:11:00,120
And therefore, I believe that looking at the history

167
00:11:00,120 --> 00:11:04,900
of the collapse of communism in those other regions of the world

168
00:11:04,900 --> 00:11:10,820
does not give us a very good handle on what's likely to happen in China.

